{
  "stem": "15686.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That I experienced personally, it did not go much further than what I've already told you about, but I saw all around me things that were happening as a result of the new laws and new decrees-- anti-Semitic decrees-- that came out from the government all the time.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It just never stopped.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every month there was a new decree.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It started out with the schools, then it went to things like the swimming pools, as I told you.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then it went to the movie theaters where at first there would be one or two where Jews were allowed to go.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The others had big signs on their box office, fur juden verboten, which meant forbidden for Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So you didn't go in there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then it went to the coffee houses, which was a very popular German pastime.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everybody went to have coffee and cake at 4:00 in the afternoon, my parents no exception.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then they closed that down, and Jews were not allowed to go there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then a decree came out that any store owned by a Jewish proprietor had to have the proprietor's name painted on the store window in one-foot high letters-- actually about 50 centimeters-- very large-- and this identified the store as a Jewish store.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Jews were allowed to buy in any store they wanted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That is one thing-- right they never took away, to spend the money and the non-Jewish stores.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Gentiles, when they went into a Jewish store, were hassled by the stormtroopers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Usually there would be one or two loitering near those stores, and if they saw people that looked quote unquote 'Aryan' go into the store, meaning they were blond, they were blue eyed, they were not Jewish looking.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
